  "doc_id": "47635",
  "text": "In this section, we introduce the technical details of disentangling the identity vector and the attribute vector using network I and network A, respectively. In our training data, we only have the annotation of the identity of each face, without any annotation of the attribute information. This is because face images with category annotations are relatively easy to obtain. Many large datasets are publically available, such as the FaceScrub [CITATION_1] , CASIAWebFace [CITATION_2] and MS-Celeb-1M [CITATION_3] datasets. However, the annotation of attributes is often more difficult, and sometimes even impossible, such for illumination and the background.",
